
- Clone the FEMuS source code from the github repo:

   git clone https://github.com/FeMTTU/femus.git

- Install petsc and libmesh in some common directory "my_external_directory" (please put it outside of the femus repo directory)

  If they are not installed already, the script "install_external.sh" in contrib/scripts/ will do it automatically, with the following syntax:
  
  ./contrib/scripts/install_external.sh --prefix-external my_external_directory

###### How to configure (command line procedure) ###########
   cd femus

   source contrib/scripts/configure_femus.sh

   fm_set_femus --prefix my_femus_absolute_path --prefix-external my_external_absolute_path --method-petsc [opt,dbg] --method-libmesh [opt,dbg]

   mkdir femus.build

   cd femus.build

   cmake -G "Unix Makefiles" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE="[Debug Release RelWithDebInfo MinSizeRel None]" -DBUILD_DOCUMENTATION="[OFF ON]"  -DLIBMESH_DIR=my_libmesh_directory   ../femus